      },
      "date": "2012-06-26 06:29:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(5 inline comments)\n\nHi Vitaly,\n\nPer the latest Lustre coding guidelines http://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/PUB/Coding+Guidelines:\n\nThe use of tabs for indentation is a reversal from previous Lustre coding guidelines, since May 2012. This is being done in order to facilitate code integration with the Linux kernel. All new patches should be submitted using tabs for ALL modified lines in the patch. If there are 6 or fewer lines using spaces for indentation between two lines changed by a patch, then all of the intervening lines should also have the indentation changed to use tabs.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
